 EVALUATION PROCEDURES                                            3234 1451
                                                                  3234 1451
 Adopted procedures are based on careful theoretical analysis     3234 1451
 utilizing available experimental data, including optical model   3234 1451
 parameter search and nuclear reaction model calculations.        3234 1451
                                                                  3234 1451
 OM parameter search was performed to reporduce measured total    3234 1451
cross section for natural Ge with the code CCOM by O. Iwamoto.    3234 1451
                                                                  3234 1451
 Nuclear reaction model calculations were performed with the      3234 1451
 code EMPIRE-II by M. Herman [He01, He02]. This is modularized    3234 1451
 statistical model code that integrates into a single system a    3234 1451
 number of important modules and features:                        3234 1451
                                                                  3234 1451
 - Spherical OM (code SCAT2 by O. Bersillone), and deformed OM    3234 1451
   including coupled-channels model (code ECIS03 by J. Raynal).   3234 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including HRTW width         3234 1451
   fluctuation correction.                                        3234 1451
 - Qauntum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION & TRISTAN by     3234 1451
   H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model.                                 3234 1451
 - Exciton model (code DEGAS by E. Betak). This code represents   3234 1451
   good approximation to DSD capture model.                       3234 1451
 - Iwamoto-Harada cluster emission model (code PCROSS).           3234 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of each particle,    3234 1451
   including realistic treatment of discrete transitions.         3234 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL-2 library [Ri03].             3234 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses, level density, 3234 1451
   discrete levels, OM parameters and gamma strength functions.   3234 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (utility code EMPEND by A. Trkov), coupled   3234 1451
   to grahpical presentation (utility code ZVView by V.Zerkin).   3234 1451
                                                                  3234 1451
